THERE'S rarely anything grey about colourful Glasgow writer and painter Alasdair Gray. Pictures add colour to Gray day THERE'S rarely anything grey about colourful Glasgow writer and painter Alasdair Gray.The man many describe as Scotland's greatest living artist was at Glasgow's Kelvingrove Museum and Art Gallery for the opening of a retrospective of his work that coincides with other shows at Glasgow Print Studio and the Gallery of Modern Art.As featured in last night's Evening Times, the shows mark the artist's 80th birthday. The 150 works at Kelvingrove include never before seen portraits and oil paintings. There are intimate portraits of family members and friends as well as landscapes. 